                <h1>Sicily: A Tapestry of History and Culture</h1>
                <p>Sicily's history is rich and diverse, shaped by various civilizations. Founded by the ancient Greeks, it later fell under Roman, Byzantine, Arab, and Spanish rule. Each culture influenced the island's architecture, language, and cuisine, making it a melting pot of traditions. The struggle for independence continued until Sicily became part of unified Italy in 1861.</p>
